      • generateParams

        private String generateParams​(Class<?>[] params,
                              boolean flag)
        Generated correct String java code enumeration of parameters with type or without type argument.

        Method takes specified array of Class. It's type tokens of parameters. And generated correct java code: enumeration of parameters with type or without type argument. How in signature of method or constructor.

        Example: ([Object] a0, [Object] a1, ...).

        Parameters:
        params - are array of Class.
        flag - is true then generated with type argument else without.
        Returns:
        correct for compilation java code String parameters.

      • implMethod

        private String implMethod​(Method method)
        Generated correct java code String implements body of the specified Method.

        If specified Method return void.class token then java code implemented this method is "". Else if return type token is primitive, then if this primitive type token == boolean.class then code implemented this method is return false; for other primitives return 0;. If specified Method return not primitive token. Java code implemented this method is return null;.

        Parameters:
        method - is Method to implement his body.
        Returns:
        String implemented body of specified Method.

      • generateMethod

        private String generateMethod​(Method method)
        Generated correct java code String that fully implements the specified Method.

        Method implemented will have:

        • access identifier is public
        • Return type == Method.getReturnType()
        • Name of method == Method.getName()
        • Enumeration of parameters == generateParams(java.lang.Class<?>[], boolean)
        • Enumeration of exceptions == generateThrowException(java.lang.reflect.Executable)
        • Body of this method == implMethod(java.lang.reflect.Method)
        Example: public Object action(java.lang.Object a0, java.lang.String a1) { return null; }
        Parameters:
        method - is Method to implement.
        Returns:
        String fully implements specified Method.

      • generateThrowException

        private String generateThrowException​(Executable executable)
        Generated correct java code String of exceptions the specified Executable.

        If specified Executable don't have exceptions then java code implemented this exceptions is "". Else exceptions separated by a comma, after world throws.

        Example: throws IOException, ImplerException

        Parameters:
        executable - gives his exceptions.
        Returns:
        String of exceptions specified Executable.

      • generateConstructor

        private String generateConstructor​(Constructor<?> constructor)
        Generated correct java code String that fully implements the specified Constructor.

        Constructor implemented will have:

        • access identifier is public
        • Name of constructor == Constructor.getDeclaringClass() + Impl
        • Enumeration of parameters == generateParams(java.lang.Class<?>[], boolean)
        • Enumeration of exceptions == generateThrowException(java.lang.reflect.Executable)
        • Body of this constructor == super(generateParams(java.lang.Class<?>[], boolean) with flag == false)
        Example: public ExampleImpl(Object a0) throws IOException { super(a0);}
        Parameters:
        constructor - is Constructor to implement.
        Returns:
        String fully implements specified Constructor

      • implMethods

        private String implMethods​(Class<?> aClass)
        Generated correct java code String that implements all Method the specified aClass and all of his ancestors.

        All methods class token and his ancestors put in HashSet wrappers over Method for correct compare of method. Not public methods get climbing the parse tree and calling Class.getDeclaredMethods().

        Parameters:
        aClass - Class is interface or class to implement.
        Returns:
        String that implements all Method.

      • implConstructors

        private String implConstructors​(Class<?> aClass)
                         throws ImplerException
        Generated correct java code String that implements all Constructor the specified aClass.

        If Class aClass == Interface then java code implemented constructors is "". Else all not private constructors implemented generateConstructor(java.lang.reflect.Constructor<?>) and append in StringBuilder.

        Parameters:
        aClass - is Class that given constructors Constructor to implement.
        Returns:
        String that implements all Constructor.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - when don't find Constructor at the specified Class.

      • getPackage

        private String getPackage​(Class<?> aClass)
        Generated correct java code String that implements Package the specified aClass Class.

        If Class.getPackageName() == "" then java code implements this package is "". Else return String "package " + aClass.getPackageName().

        Parameters:
        aClass - is Class that given Package to implement.
        Returns:
        String that implements Package.

        Header class implemented will have:

        • Name of header == + Impl.java
